103/*
104 * pmap_prot.h
105 * Protocol for the local binder service, or pmap.
106 *
107 * Copyright (C) 1984, Sun Microsystems, Inc.
108 *
109 * The following procedures are supported by the protocol:
110 *
111 * PMAPPROC_NULL() returns ()
112 * takes nothing, returns nothing
113 *
114 * PMAPPROC_SET(struct pmap) returns (bool_t)
115 * TRUE is success, FALSE is failure. Registers the tuple
116 * [prog, vers, prot, port].
117 *
118 * PMAPPROC_UNSET(struct pmap) returns (bool_t)
119 * TRUE is success, FALSE is failure. Un-registers pair
120 * [prog, vers]. prot and port are ignored.
121 *
122 * PMAPPROC_GETPORT(struct pmap) returns (long unsigned).
123 * 0 is failure. Otherwise returns the port number where the pair
124 * [prog, vers] is registered. It may lie!
125 *
126 * PMAPPROC_DUMP() RETURNS (struct pmaplist *)
127 *
128 * PMAPPROC_CALLIT(unsigned, unsigned, unsigned, string<>)
129 * RETURNS (port, string<>);
130 * usage: encapsulatedresults = PMAPPROC_CALLIT(prog, vers, proc, encapsulatedargs);
131 * Calls the procedure on the local machine. If it is not registered,
132 * this procedure is quite; ie it does not return error information!!!
133 * This procedure only is supported on rpc/udp and calls via
134 * rpc/udp. This routine only passes null authentication parameters.
135 * This file has no interface to xdr routines for PMAPPROC_CALLIT.
136 *
137 * The service supports remote procedure calls on udp/ip or tcp/ip socket 111.
138 */
139
140#define SUNRPC_PMAPPORT ((uint16_t)111)
141#define SUNRPC_PMAPPROG ((uint32_t)100000)
142#define SUNRPC_PMAPVERS ((uint32_t)2)
143#define SUNRPC_PMAPVERS_PROTO ((uint32_t)2)
144#define SUNRPC_PMAPVERS_ORIG ((uint32_t)1)
145#define SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_NULL ((uint32_t)0)
146#define SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_SET ((uint32_t)1)
147#define SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_UNSET ((uint32_t)2)
148#define SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_GETPORT ((uint32_t)3)
149#define SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_DUMP ((uint32_t)4)
150#define SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_CALLIT ((uint32_t)5)
151
152struct sunrpc_pmap {
153 uint32_t pm_prog;
154 uint32_t pm_vers;
155 uint32_t pm_prot;
156 uint32_t pm_port;
157};
158
159static const struct tok proc2str[] = {
160 { SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_NULL, "null" },
161 { SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_SET, "set" },
162 { SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_UNSET, "unset" },
163 { SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_GETPORT, "getport" },
164 { SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_DUMP, "dump" },
165 { SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_CALLIT, "call" },
166 { 0, NULL }
167};
168
169/* Forwards */
170static char *progstr(uint32_t);
171
172void
173sunrpcrequest_print(netdissect_options *ndo, register const u_char *bp,
174 register u_int length, register const u_char *bp2)
175{
176 register const struct sunrpc_msg *rp;
177 register const struct ip *ip;
178 register const struct ip6_hdr *ip6;
179 uint32_t x;
180 char srcid[20], dstid[20]; /*fits 32bit*/
181
182 rp = (const struct sunrpc_msg *)bp;
183
184 if (!ndo->ndo_nflag) {
185 snprintf(srcid, sizeof(srcid), "0x%x",
186 EXTRACT_32BITS(&rp->rm_xid));
187 strlcpy(dstid, "sunrpc", sizeof(dstid));
188 } else {
189 snprintf(srcid, sizeof(srcid), "0x%x",
190 EXTRACT_32BITS(&rp->rm_xid));
191 snprintf(dstid, sizeof(dstid), "0x%x", SUNRPC_PMAPPORT);
192 }
193
194 switch (IP_V((const struct ip *)bp2)) {
195 case 4:
196 ip = (const struct ip *)bp2;
197 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s.%s > %s.%s: %d",
198 ipaddr_string(ndo, &ip->ip_src), srcid,
199 ipaddr_string(ndo, &ip->ip_dst), dstid, length));
200 break;
201 case 6:
202 ip6 = (const struct ip6_hdr *)bp2;
203 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s.%s > %s.%s: %d",
204 ip6addr_string(ndo, &ip6->ip6_src), srcid,
205 ip6addr_string(ndo, &ip6->ip6_dst), dstid, length));
206 break;
207 default:
208 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s.%s > %s.%s: %d", "?", srcid, "?", dstid, length));
209 break;
210 }
211
212 ND_PRINT((ndo, " %s", tok2str(proc2str, " proc #%u",
213 EXTRACT_32BITS(&rp->rm_call.cb_proc))));
214 x = EXTRACT_32BITS(&rp->rm_call.cb_rpcvers);
215 if (x != 2)
216 ND_PRINT((ndo, " [rpcver %u]", x));
217
218 switch (EXTRACT_32BITS(&rp->rm_call.cb_proc)) {
219
220 case SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_SET:
221 case SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_UNSET:
222 case SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_GETPORT:
223 case SUNRPC_PMAPPROC_CALLIT:
224 x = EXTRACT_32BITS(&rp->rm_call.cb_prog);
225 if (!ndo->ndo_nflag)
226 ND_PRINT((ndo, " %s", progstr(x)));
227 else
228 ND_PRINT((ndo, " %u", x));
229 ND_PRINT((ndo, ".%u", EXTRACT_32BITS(&rp->rm_call.cb_vers)));
230 break;
231 }
232}
233
234static char *
235progstr(uint32_t prog)
236{
237#if defined(HAVE_GETRPCBYNUMBER) && defined(HAVE_RPC_RPC_H)
238 register struct rpcent *rp;
239#endif
240 static char buf[32];
241 static uint32_t lastprog = 0;
242
243 if (lastprog != 0 && prog == lastprog)
244 return (buf);
245#if defined(HAVE_GETRPCBYNUMBER) && defined(HAVE_RPC_RPC_H)
246 rp = getrpcbynumber(prog);
247 if (rp == NULL)
248#endif
249 (void) snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "#%u", prog);
250#if defined(HAVE_GETRPCBYNUMBER) && defined(HAVE_RPC_RPC_H)
251 else
252 strlcpy(buf, rp->r_name, sizeof(buf));
253#endif
254 return (buf);
255}
